				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you try to use vertical split mode with smooth scrolling while in &quot;CL&quot; mode, it'll fetch different tiles correctly but the contents of the tiles will use the same scroll offset as the non-split region.<br /><br />Nintendulator's MMC5 code actually defaults to using &quot;CL&quot; mode (there's a commented &quot;#define MMC5_EXTENDED_VSPLIT&quot;) because emulating SL mode requires a bit more CPU power; additionally, the only game which uses vertical split mode (宇宙警備隊 SDF) does not rely on SL mode (it always does vertical scrolling in multiples of 8 pixels).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
