						<div class="postbody">These things are some reasons why I proposed MMC5 submapper number to indicate SL and CL mode.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Quietust wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">If you try to use vertical split mode with smooth scrolling while in &quot;CL&quot; mode, it'll fetch different tiles correctly but the contents of the tiles will use the same scroll offset as the non-split region.</div>Is that like what I thought it would do (although I didn't explain it very well)? Perhaps I can explan what I mean something like this (if the scrolling offset is four lines):<div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">00<br />01<br />02<br />03<br />14<br />15<br />16<br />17<br />10<br />11<br />12<br />13<br />24<br />25<br />26<br />27<br />etc<br /></div><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">SL doesn't allow smooth horizontal scrolling, so most of the scrolling would need to be vertical.</div>I didn't know that. I suppose I can kind of guess why that is, though.</div>

					
